title: "Aromaticity of Large Language Models: Stable Cognitive Tendencies and the Rebound Effect in Multi-Agent Debate"
authors:
  - family-names: "Xu"
    given-names: "Zhizhan"
      alias: "XC"
version: "v1"
date-released: 2026-06-28
repository-code: "https://github.com/XC000XC/Aromaticity"
url: "https://github.com/XC000XC/Aromaticity"
abstract: "This paper proposes the concept of Model Aromaticity — the degree of stubbornness exhibited by large language models in complex judgments due to their stable cognitive tendencies. Through a reproducible five-stage debate paradigm, the study demonstrates that LLMs exhibit 'contextual compliance yet dispositional retention' under rebuttal pressure. Preprint paper and related project materials for the Aromaticity project."
